    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#frigerio1997"/>, p. 64, n. <citedRange>3</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2168</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1998"/>, pp. <citedRange>274-279</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>084800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.32</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Νέβριχος">Νέβριχος</name> <space extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀριστοτέλης" type="patronymic">Ἀριστοτέλευς</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Nebrikhos fils d'Aristotélès.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Nebrichos son of Aristoteles.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Nebrichos figlio di Aristoteles.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
	<p>Gasperini suggested that this man was the father of Mnasistrata (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr084600</ref>) and of Aristoteles son of Nebrichos 
	    (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr084700</ref>). For the latter relation, alternate name and father's name inside the same tomb is a very strong argument 
	    and the lettering of the present inscription, which seems somewhat older, induces to place both men in the above said chronology.</p>
                <p>On the name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Νέβριχος</foreign> see <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2010"/>, pp. <citedRange>98-99</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div></body>
